23
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:41,430
Remember.

24
00:02:42,230 --> 00:02:43,300
Take a bag of plums with you.

25
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,380
If someone asks where you bought them,

26
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,829
you say you bought them in front of the Xinyue Ball Room.

27
00:02:45,829 --> 00:02:47,100
If someone asks whether the plums are sweet,

28
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,560
you say they're very sour.

29
00:02:49,350 --> 00:02:50,829
10, 15, 30.

30
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,290
Clockwise, anticlockwise, clockwise.

31
00:02:58,190 --> 00:02:59,030
Bye.

32
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,950
Sorry, sir.

33
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,020
I apologize for the poor treatment.

34
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:19,540
Zeng Jiwu,

35
00:03:19,829 --> 00:03:20,870
from Scott Road.

36
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:23,140
Nice to meet you, Officer Zeng.

37
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,540
I heard

38
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:29,960
that Captain Ou often comes here, right?

39
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:31,790
So you and Captain Ou are colleagues.

40
00:03:31,790 --> 00:03:33,720
That's right. He comes here often.

41
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:37,180
Where is he now?

42
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:39,880
He didn't come here today.

43
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:46,770
Nice place.

44
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,250
The girls here are nice.

45
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:49,180
The wine is nice,

46
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:51,280
and so is your hall.

47
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:52,230
Just a small business.

48
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:53,340
All thanks to you.

49
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,630
If you like, please come here anytime.

50
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,660
What do you mean by that, sir?

51
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:04,790
I want you

52
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,780
to come to Scott Road

53
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:08,830
and try our wine.

54
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:59,260
[Oz Ball Room]

55
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:12,440
[Oz Ball Room]

56
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:41,300
Stop looking.

57
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,630
Scatter! Stop looking!

58
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,470
Ou Xiao'an!

59
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:18,630
Ou Xiao'an!

60
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,220
Ou Xiao'an!

61
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,430
Break down the door.

62
00:06:33,990 --> 00:06:34,990
Who is it?

63
00:06:36,370 --> 00:06:37,700
Captain Zeng, it's you.

64
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,730
Why are you here?

65
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,770
Who are you looking for?

66
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:47,240
You've been home all night?

67
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,530
I'm cooking. Can't you see?

68
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,300
You can cook?

69
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:58,140
See? See for yourself.

70
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:00,590
Since you're here,

71
00:07:00,810 --> 00:07:02,220
go get a bottle of wine from the cabinet.

72
00:07:02,220 --> 00:07:03,280
Let's have a drink.

73
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:04,790
Forget the wine.

74
00:07:04,970 --> 00:07:06,300
Ohashi wants to see you.

75
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:08,060
Now?

76
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:16,440
Why does Ohashi want to see me in the interrogation room?

77
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,840
We just caught a big fish.

78
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,350
So, he wants to interrogate him personally.

79
00:07:19,350 --> 00:07:20,260
What big fish?

80
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,160
You'll know when we get there.

81
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:01,380
Hello, Captain Ou.

82
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,010
Stop for now.

83
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:07,430
Yes.

84
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,630
Do you know this person?

85
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:16,870
Yes.

86
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:19,260
That's good.

87
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,910
We can interrogate him together.

88
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:22,950
We arrested that man two hours ago,

89
00:08:23,030 --> 00:08:24,060
and he is tough.

90
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,380
He hasn't

91
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:27,430
said a word so far.

92
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:31,430
What did he do?

93
00:08:32,140 --> 00:08:33,419
As far as I know,

94
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:36,500
this man has an informant on our Scott Road.

95
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,260
He also has something to do

96
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:40,030
with the fire in the clinic.

97
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,730
Chief Ohashi,

98
00:08:42,179 --> 00:08:43,299
I've had

99
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:44,700
interactions with him.

100
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:47,220
I just often have a drink at his dance hall.

101
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,940
I really don't know anything

102
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:50,140
about his identity.

103
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:56,350
Mr. Ou.

104
00:08:58,420 --> 00:08:59,620
I hope you don't mind.

105
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:02,310
I ask you here

106
00:09:02,380 --> 00:09:03,910
to help me interrogate him

107
00:09:03,990 --> 00:09:05,920
because I know you're close to him.

108
00:09:06,070 --> 00:09:06,820
Got it.

109
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:08,150
Continue.

110
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:13,430
Mr. Ou.

111
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:15,980
I'll leave it to you.

112
00:09:16,510 --> 00:09:17,430
Okay.

113
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:37,480
Would you say or not?

114
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:01,960
Mr. Lou.

115
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:03,740
Look at you.

116
00:10:04,830 --> 00:10:07,230
You could have made it as a dance hall owner.

117
00:10:09,310 --> 00:10:11,190
Why make it hard for yourself?

118
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:26,070
Who are you?

119
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:32,540
I am in your hands anyway.

120
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,060
I'm all yours.

121
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:38,740
We're kind of friends.

122
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:42,500
If you answer the questions I ask

123
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,300
properly,

124
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:49,230
I can keep you alive.

125
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:53,540
Who is you contact?

126
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:03,370
You're my contact.

127
00:11:27,070 --> 00:11:28,420
I'll ask you again.

128
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,740
Who is your contact?

129
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:34,700
You, traitor,

130
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,510
are my contact.

131
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:40,370
Kill me.

132
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:47,280
Kill me.

133
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,750
Kill me!

134
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:00,700
I've been working so hard

135
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,810
to get intel for you every day.

136
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:03,220
What if I get caught?

137
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:04,230
If you get caught,

138
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:06,660
I'll save you, even if it means risking my life.

139
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:08,060
You are a good man, then.

140
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:10,140
What if I get caught?

141
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:10,950
If you get caught,

142
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:12,590
please don't give me away.

143
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:18,680
If I get caught, you have to give me a quick death.

144
00:12:47,740 --> 00:12:49,220
Kill me.

145
00:12:59,940 --> 00:13:00,980
Mr. Ou!

146
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,430
Put the gun down.

147
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:06,020
Traitor! Japaneses' pig!

148
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:07,980
Kill me.

149
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,740
Go get Dr. Ando.

150
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:30,900
Now.

151
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:31,830
Got it!

152
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,950
I've devoted half of my life

153
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:54,710
to finding a way to make people tell the truth.

154
00:13:55,350 --> 00:13:56,500
I believe

155
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:58,790
it can get you out of the habit of lying.

156
00:14:09,430 --> 00:14:11,180
Scopolamine is good stuff.

157
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,460
It allows people to answer questions

158
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:14,390
unconsciously.

159
00:14:14,780 --> 00:14:16,150
No one I've ever met

160
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:18,470
has been able to resist it.

161
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:22,350
Let's see how Mr. Lou takes it.

162
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,640
Are you from the NBIS?

163
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,270
No.

164
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:42,390
Then you're a communist?

165
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:43,540
I...

166
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:45,750
I am.

167
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:48,310
Who is your downline?

168
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,460
Captain Ou.

169
00:15:08,670 --> 00:15:11,190
I think he said that you're his downline.

170
00:15:26,220 --> 00:15:27,900
There is no use in resisting.

171
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:30,350
People's wills can't beat science.

172
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:31,900
Ando.

173
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:12,350
Who are your upline and downline?

174
00:16:15,540 --> 00:16:18,430
My upline is...

175
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:20,140
Who is it?

176
00:16:21,310 --> 00:16:23,270
My upline is...

177
00:16:24,110 --> 00:16:26,350
Who is it? Tell me.

178
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:44,070
Arise!

179
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:49,140
All victims of oppression!

180
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:54,220
Arise!

181
00:16:55,270 --> 00:16:57,180
Did you have something to do

182
00:16:57,270 --> 00:16:58,930
with the fire in my biochemistry database?

183
00:16:58,930 --> 00:17:02,110
Who else is your informant at my place?

184
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:04,780
Tell me!

185
00:17:05,869 --> 00:17:10,550
So come, brothers and sisters,

186
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:15,250
for the struggle carries on!

187
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:24,020
The Internationale...

188
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:29,030
unites the world!

189
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:42,630
Miss Qin, you're here!

190
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:44,460
-Come on, you take care of the customer.
-Boss lady.

191
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:45,260
Has the maroon silk satin

192
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:47,070
I ordered arrived yet?

193
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:48,180
Just arrived.

194
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:49,390
Come in, please.

195
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,040
Why are you dressed like this?

196
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,740
It's easier for underground work.

197
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:57,300
The dress is just a facade.

198
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:59,270
It's your faith and your reactions

199
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:01,860
that make you a real underground worker.

200
00:18:02,630 --> 00:18:04,470
You must always remember your faith,

201
00:18:04,470 --> 00:18:05,800
rein in your reactions,

202
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:07,740
and don't let anyone

203
00:18:07,870 --> 00:18:09,460
decipher your body language

204
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:11,120
and emotions at first glance.

205
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:12,980
Got it.

206
00:18:13,590 --> 00:18:14,990
The organization is considering

207
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:16,340
your application to join the Party.

208
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:17,140
Really?

209
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:18,860
Then

210
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:20,470
I'll be a Party member soon.

211
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:23,060
When you join the Party in the future,

212
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:25,320
you should be more strict with yourself.

213
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,470
Qiushui.

214
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:31,740
I have something to report to you.

215
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:32,500
Go ahead.

216
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:34,380
I've noticed that my big brother

217
00:18:34,380 --> 00:18:37,380
has been in frequent contact with the NBIS in Chongqing.

218
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:39,980
I'm worried that he wants to move to Chongqing.

219
00:18:40,230 --> 00:18:41,820
If I leave Shanghai,

220
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:44,460
will it affect the organization's examination of me?

221
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:46,130
If you do go to Chongqing,

222
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:48,430
there will be comrades from Chongqing

223
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:49,560
to liaise with you.

224
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:54,270
Shanghai is chaotic at the moment.

225
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:55,900
The Japanese and the Chinese Nationalist Party

226
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,190
are both targeting us.

227
00:18:57,870 --> 00:18:58,910
Qiushui,

228
00:18:58,980 --> 00:19:00,740
will you stay in Shanghai?

229
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:02,910
I'll do as the organization says.

230
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:05,230
Someone has to do the work in Shanghai.

231
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,140
We're in a chaotic time.

232
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:08,550
The Japanese set up posts at every stop.

233
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:09,430
We have a lot of supplies

234
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:11,230
but can get them out of Shanghai.

235
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:13,500
Do we lack passes?

236
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,660
My brother is a businessman.

237
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,960
It won't be hard for him to get the passes.

238
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,060
Leave it to me, Qiushui.

239
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:32,390
They are very sensitive about the passes now.

240
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:33,790
Be careful.

241
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:36,510
Don't worry.

242
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:37,990
You got the wrong person.

243
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,470
You must have caught the wrong person!

244
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:40,180
Let me go!

245
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:41,860
I really don't know anything!

246
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:44,760
I really don't know anything!

247
00:19:44,910 --> 00:19:46,910
I really don't know anything. I really...

248
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:47,220
[Student of Shanghai Aurora University School of Medicine
Liao Shuyun]

249
00:19:47,780 --> 00:19:49,350
I really don't know anything!

250
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,060
I really don't know anything!

251
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:52,790
Looks like you have read many books by Ye Xuanmin.

252
00:19:52,910 --> 00:19:54,150
You're a hardcore anti-Japanese.

253
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:55,190
Captain Ou.

254
00:19:55,390 --> 00:19:57,140
No. No.

255
00:19:55,460 --> 00:19:57,670
[Student of Shanghai Aurora University School of Medicine
Zheng Bangyao]

256
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:59,030
I've only been to one reading party.

257
00:19:59,030 --> 00:20:00,290
I really know nothing.

258
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:01,460
You don't know?

259
00:20:01,850 --> 00:20:03,250
Then your trip to the reading party is in vain, right?

260
00:20:03,130 --> 00:20:04,720
[Ye Xuanmin Collection]

261
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:17,510
Are you hurt?

262
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:18,850
I'm fine.

263
00:20:19,490 --> 00:20:20,730
Come, come with me.

264
00:20:20,930 --> 00:20:21,730
Come on.

265
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:24,280
I remembered.

266
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:25,820
I remembered.

267
00:20:26,180 --> 00:20:26,980
I heard

268
00:20:27,090 --> 00:20:29,070
that Ye Xuanmin has come to Shanghai.

269
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:30,690
And I saw him

270
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:32,300
wearing a black hat.

271
00:20:40,060 --> 00:20:41,670
You know Ye Xuanmin very well?

272
00:20:41,670 --> 00:20:42,870
I-I-I don't know him.

273
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:43,900
I don't know him.

274
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:46,260
How did you know he came to Shanghai if you don't know him?

275
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:47,620
I saw his photos.

276
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:49,870
I can't be mistaken.

277
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:51,940
Are you sure?

278
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:55,020
I'm sure. I'm sure.

279
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,080
Ye Xuanmin.

280
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:02,780
I can finally meet you.

281
00:21:08,460 --> 00:21:09,500
Liao Shuyun,

282
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:12,220
you should've learned from Zheng Bangyao.

283
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:14,280
So you wouldn't get whipped too much.

284
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:17,770
Zheng Bangyao, you bastard!

285
00:21:17,950 --> 00:21:19,140
You traitor!

286
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:23,740
What are you doing?

287
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,420
Are you out of your mind?

